(asumsi.co, 31 Jul 2018)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralFEAR OF HEIGHTSShe took some convincing to try the sport given that she had a fear of heights. "I never had the thought of becoming an athlete, especially paragliding. I was afraid of heights. But my father was very persuasive and I was just going with it. And I remember I was unable to open my eyes in my first tandem training. I was very scared." (asumsi.co, 31 Jul 2018)RETIREMENT PLANSShe has contemplated retiring after the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. "I am no longer the world champion. I can see much younger and more talented paragliders in the national team. So I think it is time for me to retire after the Asian Games." (asumsi.co, 31 Jul 2018) '), ('Nickname', 'Lis (asumsi.co, 31 Jul 2018)'), ('Injuries', 'In September 2016 her right ankle was injured due to a bad landing at the 2016 National Games [PON] in Bandung, Indonesia. (SportsDeskOnline, 08 Aug 2016)EARLY DAYSHis father worked as a paddle rickshaw driver and his mother a vegetable trader. As a boy he used to work herding goats, which he says taught him how to be responsible. "If I lost a goat, I had to pay for it. We were poor. We had to be careful doing our job." (bola.com, 17 Jun 2018; thejakartapost.com, 21 Jul 2010; suarakarya-online.com, 03 Jul 2008) '), ('Hero', 'Portuguese footballer Cristiano Ronaldo. (radarsemarang.com, 14 Jun 2018)'), ('Injuries', 'In 2016 he suffered a knee injury that affected his preparation throughout 2017 leading up to the South East Asian Games in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. name: Maria Natalia
bio: [('Beginning', 'She began competing in long jump and triple jump events at age 12. She initially began athletics while in primary school in Bali, Indonesia. In the fifth grade her father took her to a field where she saw professional athletes training, including national athlete and coach I Ketut Pageh. He noticed her talent and encouraged her to start training at school, and eventually began coaching her in her teens. (viva.co.id, 09 Dec 2017; rappler.com, 23 July 2016; Athlete, 29 Sep 2014; Media Indonesia, 13 Jul 2008)'), ('Reason', 'She was inspired to take up the sport after watching coach I Ketut Pageh training with his team in a field. She was also influenced by her parents and teacher. "One of the reasons why I chose to jump was that I don\'t like running." (Athlete, 29 Sep 2014; koran-jakarta.com, 25 Dec 2013)'), ('Debut', '2007 for Indonesia (Athlete, 29 Sep 2014)'), ('Coach', 'I Ketut Pageh [personal], INA (sport.detik.com, 29 Mar 2018)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. (sport.detik.com, 29 Mar 2018)'), ('Awards', 'She was the flag bearer for Indonesia at the opening ceremony of the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro. (olympic.org, 05 Aug 2016)In 2014 she received an Achievement Award from the Indonesian National Sports Committee. (thebalipost.com, 10 Mar 2014; detik.com, 07 Mar 2014)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralINJURY AFFECTS ASIAN GAMES PREPThe injury she suffered at the 2015 South East Asian Games continued to disrupt her training over the next few years, including her preparation for the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. "It is quite hard to bring back my confidence with my post-injury condition and at the same time deal with the pressure of hosting the [2018 Asian] Games. But my coach has been supportive and telling me to just relax and follow the process. So I decided to practice smarter. I realise my sport is very technical which demands full concentration." (bola.com, 16 Jun 2018; sport.detik.com, 29 Mar 2018)INCHEON DEDICATIONAfter winning the gold medal in the long jump at the 2014 Asian Games in Incheon, Republic of Korea, she dedicated the victory to her late father. "I would give back my medals if I could have my father back, but of course this is not possible. I promised myself that I had to win for him and become better than he had ever known." (thejakartapost.com, 01 Oct 2014)MEDICAL CONDITIONShe suffered from restricted blood flow in her legs as a child. She underwent surgery to correct the issue, but this resulted in her left leg being slightly longer than her right leg. (sinarharapan.co, 02 Oct 2014; straitstimes.com, 31 Jul 2016) '), ('Hero', 'US athlete Carl Lewis. (cnnindonesia.com, 22 Jan 2015; Athlete, 29 Sep 2014)'), ('Influence', 'Her family, and coach I Ketut Pageh. (koran-jakarta.com, 25 Dec 2013)'), ('Relatives', 'Her partner Kadek Sukaryate has competed in long jump at national level in Indonesia. (tribunnews.com, 02 Jul 2017)'), ('Nickname', 'Mary (viva.co.id, 09 Sep 2017)'), ('Injuries', 'She injured a tendon in her left leg at the 2015 South East Asian Games in Singapore, but still went on to win a gold medal in the triple jump at the event. She required a break from the sport to rehabilitate the injury in 2015, and her training was still impacted by the problem through to 2018. (thejakartapost.com, 23 Aug 2017; sport.detik.com, 29 Mar 2018)An ankle injury meant she was unable to compete at the 2007 South East Asian Games in Nakhon Ratchasima, Thailand. (suarakarya-online.com, 07 Nov 2007)'), ('Education', 'Teaching - Institute of Teacher Training and Education PGRI Bali, Bali, INA'), ('Languages', 'English, Indonesian'), ('Highlights', 'RankEventYearLocationResultAsian Games1Long Jump2014Incheon, KOR6.5510Triple Jump2014Incheon, KOR13.39Olympic GamesQualificationLong Jump2016Rio de Janeiro, BRA6.29World ChampionshipsQualificationTriple Jump2007Osaka, JPN12.94South East Asian Games1Long Jump2015Singapore, SIN6.701Triple Jump2015Singapore, SIN13.751Long Jump2013Naypyidaw, MYA6.391Triple Jump2013Naypyidaw, MYA14.172Long Jump2017Kuala Lumpur, MAS6.472Triple Jump2017Kuala Lumpur, MAS13.522Long Jump2011Indonesia6.472Triple Jump2011Indonesia13.733Long Jump2009Vientiane, LAO6.233Triple Jump2009Vientiane, LAO13.31')]

name: GREYSIA
bio: [('Beginning', 'She began playing badminton at age five in Manado, Indonesia. At age eight she decided that she wanted to pursue the sport seriously, so her family moved to Jakarta to support her training. She joined the national training setup in 2003. (manadopostonline.com, 28 Dec 2017; olahraga.kompas.com, 31 Oct 2014)'), ('Reason', 'She was inspired by Indonesian players Ricky Subagja and Rexy Mainaky. "Every time I watched Ricky and Rexy on television, I always imagined how would it be like to travel around the world by playing badminton. I was lucky that we had a small badminton field in the area. I always went there to play after watching those badminton stars on television." (olahraga.kompas.com, 31 Oct 2014)'), ('Coach', 'Eng Hian [national], INA (juara.bolasport.com, 08 Mar 2018)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia, and win an Olympic or world championship gold medal. (cnnindonesia.com, 02 Jul 2016; jawapos.com, 07 Jun 2018)'), ('Memorable', "Winning gold in the women's doubles at the 2014 Asian Games in Incheon, Republic of Korea, which was the first Indonesian women's doubles gold medal at an Asian Games since 1978. (badzine.net, 28 Sep 2014; kumparan.com, 17 Mar 2018; SportsDeskOnline, 12 Jun 2018)"), ('Additional Information', "GeneralLONGEST MATCHShe and her former partner Nitya Krishinda Maheswari set a record for the longest international women's doubles match while playing Japanese pair Kurumi Yonao and Naoko Fukuman in the semifinal of the 2016 Asian Championships in Wuhan, People's Republic of China. Polii and Mahessawari eventually lost the 161-minute long match 13-21, 21-19, 24-22. (bwfbadminton.com, 30 Apr 2016)OLYMPIC DISQUALIFICATIONShe and former partner Meiliana Jauhari were disqualified from the women's doubles competition at the 2012 Olympic Games in London, after a Badminton World Federation [BWF] disciplinary committee ruled they had deliberately attempted to lose a group match in order to manipulate the draw for the knockout stage. The pair were charged by the BWF with 'not using one's best efforts to win a match', and 'conducting oneself in a manner that is abusive or detrimental to the sport'. In addition, both players were suspended for four months by the Badminton Association of Indonesia. The BWF also disqualified three other pairs for committing the same offences during the women's doubles tournament at the Games. name: DELLIE
bio: [('Beginning', 'She took up archery at age five in Surabaya, Indonesia. Her mother was a national archery athlete and always took her along to practice. She eventually asked her mother to teach her and at age seven she began competing in regional competitions. (thestar.com.my, 19 Aug 2017; surabaya.tribunnews.com, 04 Dec 2016; sport.detik.com, 10 Apr 2018)'), ('Reason', '"I wouldn\'t have been an archer if not for my mum, I followed her to the archery range almost every day. Then, when I was just five, she gave me a tiny little bow and arrow to try out at a 5m target in our backyard. From that moment, I told her, \'Mum, I want to be just like you.\'" (thestar.com.my, 19 Aug 2017)'), ('Debut', '2002 for Indonesia (Athlete, 26 Aug 2018)'), ('Coach', 'Denny Trisyanto [national, father], INA; Lilies Heliarti [national, aunt]; Nurfitriyana Saiman [national], INA (bola.com, 10 Apr 2018; sport.detik.com, 10 Apr 2018)'), ('Ambition', 'To win a gold medal at the Asian Games and world championships. (sport.detik.com, 10 Apr 2018)'), ('Memorable', 'Winning two medals at the 2013 South East Asian Games in Naypyidaw, Myanmar. (Athlete, 26 Aug 2018)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralCOMPETING AGAINST FAMILYAt the 2007 Asian Archery Grand Prix in Isfahan, Islamic Republic of Iran, she competed against her mother Lilies Handayani. "It was an amazing moment. We were both representing Indonesia. I was still 17 and I got to meet her in the final. We both got very competitive." Her mother won 107-105, saying "I played all out even though she [Dellie] is my daughter." (sport.detik.com, 11 Apr 2018; antaranews.com, 28 Oct 2007) DISCIPLINE SWITCHShe initially competed in recurve archery before switching to compound in order to compete alongside her mother Lilies Handayani and aunt Lilies Heliarti. The trio won a silver medal in the team competition at the 2007 World Cup event in Dover, England. (thestar.com.my, 19 Aug 2017; worldarchery.org, 04 Aug 2007) '), ('Hero', 'Her mother Lilies Handayani. (Athlete, 26 Aug 2018)'), ('Influence', 'Her mother Lilies Handayani. (Athlete, 26 Aug 2018)'), ('Relatives', "Her mother Lilies Handayani has represented Indonesia in archery, and won a silver medal in the women's team event at the 1988 Olympic Games in Seoul. Her aunt Lilies Heliarti, and younger sisters Della Adisty Handayani and Putera Irvaldi Ananda, have also represented Indonesia in archery. bio: [('Beginning', 'He took up judo in 2012 and joined a kurash team in 2017. (luckyramadhan.com, 14 Jul 2018)'), ('Reason', '"I wanted to become a motorbike racer, but my parents didn\'t agree. (luckyramadhan.com, 14 Jul 2018)'), ('Debut', '2018 for Indonesia (Athlete, 17 Aug 2018)'), ('Coach', 'Sugiri Wijaya [national], INA; Deni Zulfendri [national], INA (galamedianews.com, 23 Jul 2018; medan.tribunnews.com, 27 Mar 2018)'), ('Training', 'In preparation for the 2018 Asian Games he trained at the National Training Centre in Bogor, Indonesia. (luckyramadhan.com, 14 Jul 2018)'), ('Ambition', 'To win a medal at the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. (luckyramadhan.com, 14 Jul 2018)'), ('Memorable', 'Competing at the 2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games in Ashgabat, Turkmenistan, and being selected to compete at 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. (Athlete, 17 Aug 2018)'), ('Additional Information', 'General"I originally wanted to be a motor racer but since the cost was too expensive, I turned to athletics [sprint]. My parents introduced me to a coach and I remember I was told to chase some kids who were already practising. So I did and I managed to catch up with them and won. The coach praised me for that. I had the chance to win a junior tournament in sprint. At senior high, my friend Yoga invited me to a judo practice. I remember watching them slamming each other. I began curious, interested and eventually join them. After a year of practice, I managed to win a tournament and I have not thought to switch sports again because basically I like all sports, as a hobby." '), ('Influence', 'His parents. I accepted the offer and on the first practice session I was almost drowned because I did not know how to swim." (berisik.id, 12 Feb 2017)'), ('Debut', '2014 for Indonesia, Asian Cup in Singapore (Athlete, 17 Aug 2018)'), ('Coach', 'Dede Rohmat, INA (Athlete, 17 Aug 2018)'), ('Memorable', 'Competing at the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro. (Athlete, 15 Aug 2018)'), ('Hero', 'Australian rower Kim Brennan. (Athlete, 15 Aug 2018)'), ('Influence', 'Her mother. (Athlete, 15 Aug 2018)'), ('Nickname', 'Echek (Athlete, 17 Aug 2018)'), ('Injuries', 'She suffered several minor burns from accidentally being electrocuted during training at Cileunca lake, Bandung, Indonesia, in February 2018. An investigation revealed that a torn cable near the lake owned by the State Electricity Company had curved and touched the surface because of heavy rain. (cnnindonesia.com, 12 Feb 2018)She was hampered by a back injury in October 2015 and was advised to undergo surgery, but delayed the operation to compete at the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro. A month after the Olympic Games she competed at the 2016 National Sports Week [PON] in Bandung, Indonesia, which worsened the injury. The team doctor recommended a break from rowing. She rejoined the national team in December 2017. (kompas.com, 31 May 2016; wartakota.tribunnews.com, 08 Feb 2017; sport.detik.com, 16 Jan 2018)'), ('Education', 'Physical Education - University of Singaperbangsa Karawang, Indonesia'), ('Languages', 'Indonesian'), ('Hobbies', 'Futsal.
